ss loading from the file system. It handles:\n- File I/O and bytecode stream creation\n- jimage (Java runtime image) file loading for modular JDK\n- Platform-specific path canonicalization\n- Actual bytes-to-class conversion\n\n## Class Caching and Dictionary\n\n**systemDictionary.hpp and systemDictionary.cpp** (src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp and .cpp) implement the SystemDictionary, which caches all loaded classes:\n\n- **Data Structure**: Each ClassLoaderData maintains a concurrent hash table (Dictionary) with a fixed number of buckets\n- **Caching**: Once a class is fully loaded, it's added to the dictionary of the defining class loader\n- **Thread Safety**: Uses ClassLoaderData locks for individual loader operations and SystemDictionary_lock for global additions\n- **Placeholder Management**: Temporarily places (name, loader) placeholders during loading to detect ClassCircularityErrors\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `resolve_or_fail()`: Loads class if needed, throws error if not found\n  - `resolve_or_null()`: Loads class if needed, returns null if not found\n  - `find_instance_klass()`: Looks up already-loaded classes\n\n## Delegation Chain Summary\n\nThe complete delegation chain is:\n1. Application calls `ClassLoader.loadClass(name)`\n2. Parent-first check: delegates to parent → platform → bootstrap\n3. Bootstrap loader delegates to HotSpot's `findBootstrapClassOrNull()` (C++)\n4. HotSpot calls `classLoader.cpp` functions to load bytes from file system\n5. `systemDictionary` caches the loaded class for future lookups\n6. All subsequent accesses retrieve from SystemDictionary cache (fast path)\n\nThis design ensures modularity, proper class visibility, and efficient caching while maintaining the principle that classes are loaded by their defining class loader."
