  "text": "The Java class loading delegation chain in OpenJDK follows a parent-first delegation model implemented across Java and C++ layers:\n\n## Java Layer - Parent-First Delegation\n\n**ClassLoader.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java, lines 534-570) implements the core `loadClass(String name, boolean resolve)` method. The delegation chain works as follows:\n\n1. First checks if the class is already loaded via `findLoadedClass(name)`\n2. If not loaded, delegates to the parent classloader: `parent.loadClass(name, false)`\n3. If parent is null, tries to find the bootstrap class via `findBootstrapClassOrNull(name)`\n4. If still not found, calls `findClass(name)` to allow the specific loader to search\n5. Finally resolves the class if requested\n\n## Built-in Class Loaders\n\n**BuiltinClassLoader.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java, lines 89-150) serves as the base class for the three built-in loaders, extending SecureClassLoader. It supports:\n- Module-based class loading via the `loadModule` method\n- URL class path loading for classes and resources\n- A specialized delegation model that maps class names to packages and delegates accordingly\n\n**ClassLoaders.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java) creates and manages the three built-in class loaders:\n\n1. **BootClassLoader** (lines 131-140): Loads bootstrap classes, delegates to JLA.findBootstrapClassOrNull()\n2. **PlatformClassLoader** (lines 146-150): Loads platform classes and JDK runtime classes, with parent = null (inherits bootstrap loader)\n3. **AppClassLoader**: Loads application classes from the application class path, with parent = PlatformClassLoader\n\nThe static initializer (lines 63-99) sets up these loaders with proper hierarchy and class paths.\n\n## HotSpot Native Implementation\n\n**classLoader.cpp** (src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp) provides the C++ implementation for native class loading from the file system. It handles:\n- File I/O and bytecode stream creation\n- jimage (Java runtime image) file loading for modular JDK\n- Platform-specific path canonicalization\n- Actual bytes-to-class conversion\n\n## Class Caching and Dictionary\n\n**systemDictionary.hpp and systemDictionary.cpp** (src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp and .cpp) implement the SystemDictionary, which caches all loaded classes:\n\n- **Data Structure**: Each ClassLoaderData maintains a concurrent hash table (Dictionary) with a fixed number of buckets\n- **Caching**: Once a class is fully loaded, it's added to the dictionary of the defining class loader\n- **Thread Safety**: Uses ClassLoaderData locks for individual loader operations and SystemDictionary_lock for global additions\n- **Placeholder Management**: Temporarily places (name, loader) placeholders during loading to detect ClassCircularityErrors\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `resolve_or_fail()`: Loads class if needed, throws error if not found\n  - `resolve_or_null()`: Loads class if needed, returns null if not found\n  - `find_instance_klass()`: Looks up already-loaded classes\n\n## Delegation Chain Summary\n\nThe complete delegation chain is:\n1. Application calls `ClassLoader.loadClass(name)`\n2. Parent-first check: delegates to parent → platform → bootstrap\n3. Bootstrap loader delegates to HotSpot's `findBootstrapClassOrNull()` (C++)\n4. HotSpot calls `classLoader.cpp` functions to load bytes from file system\n5. `systemDictionary` caches the loaded class for future lookups\n6. All subsequent accesses retrieve from SystemDictionary cache (fast path)\n\nThis design ensures modularity, proper class visibility, and efficient caching while maintaining the principle that classes are loaded by their defining class loader."
